	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've got my GB-Z80 macros working well now, and they assemble my old wla code cleanly, save for having to convert - and + labels. These macros support the many variations of some instructions. Tested with ca65-2.13.3.<br /><br /><a href="http://blargg.8bitalley.com/gameboy/ca65-gb-z80-0.1.0.zip" class="postlink">ca65-gb-z80-0.1.0.zip</a><br /><br />Includes some demo programs that build as GB ROMs, an instruction syntax list, and a full instruction test.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
